                            <h1>
                            Inviting Others to &ldquo;Come unto Christ&rdquo;
                            </h1>
                            <h2 class="author">
                                    <div class="byline" id="">
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p2" class="">Elder Gene R. Cook</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p" class="">Of the First Quorum of the Seventy</p>
			</div>   
                                    </h2>
                            <hr>
                        </div><!-- end #details -->
                       
                        <div id="primary">
                            
                            
                            <blockquote class="intro dontHighlight">
                                        <a href="http://lds.org/church/leader/gene-r-cook?lang=eng">
                                                        <img id="talkPhoto" src="/bc/content/shared/content/images/leaders/gene-r-cook-10.jpg" alt="Gene R. Cook" class="img-decor">
                                                    </a>
                                        
                                        
                                        
                                    </blockquote>
                            
                            <span style="display: none" id="article-id">03232_000_016</span>
			<div class="figure">
				
			</div>
			<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p3" class="">Dear brethren of the priesthood, I greet you this evening in the name of the Lord <a class="no-link-style" href="http://mormon.org/jesus-christ">Jesus Christ</a> with the sacred injunction, &ldquo;Come unto <a class="no-link-style" href="http://jesuschrist.lds.org/">Christ</a>.&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/10.32?lang=eng#31" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moro. 10:32</a>.)</p>
			<div>
				<h2>A Divine Commission to Bring Souls to God</h2>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p5" class="">I testify that the Lord expects us to bring souls unto Him by inviting all men to come unto Christ, and by so doing, find Him ourselves. It truly is &ldquo;the thing &hellip; of the most worth unto you.&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/15.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 15:6</a>.) In fact, your very ordination is &ldquo;to <a class="no-link-style" href="http://lds.org/library/display/0,4945,8057-1-4424-1,00.html">preach</a> faith and repentance and remission of sins, according to [his] word&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/53.3?lang=eng#2" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 53:3</a>), &ldquo;that you may bring souls unto [him].&rdquo; It is the greatest offering that man can give to God. (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/15.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 15:6</a>; see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/29.7?lang=eng#6" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 29:7</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/17.11?lang=eng#10" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 17:11</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/29.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 29:9</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/31.34-35?lang=eng#33" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 31:34&ndash;35</a>). In fact, you &ldquo;received [your] first lessons in the world of spirits and were prepared to [labor] for the salvation of the souls of men.&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138.56?lang=eng#55" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 138:56</a>.) You cannot fail. That counsel applies to you young men as well.</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p6" class="">Perhaps we are at the time in our ministry when, in preparation for the Lord&rsquo;s second coming, when with renewed emphasis, <span class="emphasis">in love,</span> we must call men to repentance. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/6.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 6:9</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/11.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 11:9</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.14?lang=eng#13" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 18:14</a>.) We must invite them to &ldquo;come unto Christ&rdquo; testifying boldly in His name to bring the &ldquo;mighty change&rdquo; into the hearts of our people. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/5.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 5:2</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.14?lang=eng#13" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 5:14</a>.)</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h2>The Purpose of Visits to Homes</h2>
				<div class="figure">
	<ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>To exhort them &ldquo;to pray vocally and in secret&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/20.47?lang=eng#46" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 20:47</a>);</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>&ldquo;To stir them up in remembrance&rdquo; of God (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/4.19?lang=eng#18" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 4:19</a>); and</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>&ldquo;To turn [them] to the Lord with full purpose of heart&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/7.33?lang=eng#32" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 7:33</a>).</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	</ol>
      </div>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p12" class="">We do not visit the active just to &ldquo;visit,&rdquo; or the less active just to get them out to church, although that may be part of what happens. In essence, we visit to help the heads of those homes, male or female, to become the spiritual leaders in their homes, to lead their families to Christ, to pray, to fast, and to read the scriptures together. If that happens in our visits, all else will take care of itself.</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h2>&ldquo;A Preparation to Hear the Word&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/32.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 32:6</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/33.22-23?lang=eng#21" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 33:22&ndash;23</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/34.3?lang=eng#2" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 34:3</a>)</h2>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p14" class="">How can we make such visits with power and authority, as described in the scriptures, especially to the less active? The most important element in our preparation is to humble ourselves mightily before God. We must be believing. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/90.24?lang=eng#23" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 90:24</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/morm/9.27?lang=eng#26" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Morm. 9:27</a>.) We must not doubt nor fear. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/6.36?lang=eng#35" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 6:36</a>.)</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p15" class="">We must pray fervently throughout our visits that we may &ldquo;speak the thoughts that [the Lord] shall put into your hearts, and you shall not be confounded before men; for it shall be given you &hellip; in the very moment, what ye shall say.&rdquo; Even &ldquo;that portion that shall be meted unto every man.&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/100.5-6?lang=eng#4" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 100:5&ndash;6</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.85?lang=eng#84" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 84:85</a>.)</p>
				<div class="figure">
	<ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>On a first visit, a man quits smoking after twenty-five years and prays to God to know the next step.</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>A less-active man says, &ldquo;I&rsquo;ve been waiting for you.&rdquo;</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>A wife tells of her less-active husband&rsquo;s dream that &ldquo;messengers would be sent&rdquo; and says, &ldquo;We will believe whatever you tell us.&rdquo;</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>An unscheduled phone call is made at a critical moment, touching a woman who was turning to inactivity.</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	</ol>
      </div>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p21" class="">Someone said, &ldquo;Coincidences like these are God&rsquo;s little miracles wherein he desired to remain anonymous.&rdquo;</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h2>The Visits&mdash;Suggestions for Preparing Men&rsquo;s Hearts</h2>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p23" class="">Remember, not only the teacher but the learner must have the Spirit of the Lord. You, as the teacher, must do all in your power to <span class="emphasis">prepare the hearts of men</span> so the Spirit can teach. May I suggest seven scriptural performances (see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/31.10?lang=eng#9" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 31:10</a>) that, if humbly employed, will immediately invite the Spirit into your heart and the hearts of others. You may want to write them down.</p>
				<div class="figure">
	<ol class="number">
					<li>
						<span class="label">1.</span>
						<p><span class="emphasis">Pray. </span>Pray for the Spirit. Ask those you teach to pray for you and for themselves while you are teaching. Ask for discernment to understand the needs of those you visit. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/17.2-3?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 17:2&ndash;3</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/20.1?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 20:1</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/136.29,32?lang=eng#28" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 136:29, 32</a>.) For example:</p>
						<div class="figure">
	      <ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>During a visit, upon bended knee, two priesthood leaders pray that a wayward daughter will be blessed. Her parents are touched by the prayer and repent that very evening. They begin to attend church and a temple preparation seminar and now have been sealed as a <a class="no-link-style" href="http://lds.org/ensign/2003/05/the-importance-of-the-family?lang=eng">family</a>.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>A seven-year-old responds to his less-active father, who says he won&rsquo;t pray, with &ldquo;Please pray, Dad. Take Mom and me to the temple.&rdquo; That family has since been sealed.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
	      </ol>
	    </div>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label">2.</span>
						<p><span class="emphasis">Use the Scriptures. </span>They are the words of the Lord to us, and the Spirit of the Lord will speak through them to all, both young and old. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/32.3?lang=eng#2" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 32:3</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/31.5?lang=eng#4" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 31:5</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/32.4?lang=eng#3" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 32:4</a>.) For example:</p>
						<div class="figure">
	      <ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>In one of the visits, a testimony is given of a verse relating to <a class="no-link-style" href="http://lds.org/study/topics/baptism?lang=eng">baptism</a>. An investigator says, &ldquo;I do believe God sent you. I&rsquo;ll be baptized.&rdquo;</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>A scripture is read on another visit about multiplying and replenishing the earth. A young couple with one child humbly confesses their unrighteous decision to have no more children.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
	      </ol>
	    </div>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label">3.</span>
						<p><span class="emphasis">Testify. </span>If you follow His promptings, the Lord will direct you to testify frequently throughout these visits. Testify that the Lord has sent you. As you do, &ldquo;the Holy Ghost carrieth it unto the hearts of the children of men.&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/33.1?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 33:1</a>; see also <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.44-47?lang=eng#43" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 5:44&ndash;47</a>.) Let me again illustrate:</p>
						<div class="figure">
	      <ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>In his testimony, a priesthood leader unknowingly quotes a sentence verbatim from a sister&rsquo;s patriarchal blessing.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>Another visit: one member testifies to a couple of life after death from the scriptures only to learn later of the recent loss of their little one.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
	      </ol>
	    </div>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label">4.</span>
						<p><span class="emphasis">Use music. </span>Using recorded hymns or singing the songs of Zion with or to the Saints in their homes, as prompted, will always bring the Spirit of the Lord. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/25.12?lang=eng#11" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 25:12</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/26.30?lang=eng#29" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matt. 26:30</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/col/3.16?lang=eng#15" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Col. 3:16</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/1-sam/16.23?lang=eng#22" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1 Sam. 16:23</a>.) For example:</p>
						<div class="figure">
	      <ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>A priesthood leader said with a smile, &ldquo;I could never sing. I have a terrible voice. But we were prompted to do so. My voice was as the voice of an angel.&rdquo; The less-active man wept and returned to the Church.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>A home teacher said, &ldquo;I sang with his children. The crusty old fellow cried and humbled himself for the first time in years.&rdquo;</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
	      </ol>
	    </div>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label">5.</span>
						<p><span class="emphasis">Express love and <a class="no-link-style" href="http://lds.org/topic/gratitude/">gratitude</a> to God and man. </span>Express love openly for God and for His children, and the Spirit will be felt profoundly. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/13.34-35?lang=eng#33" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">John 13:34&ndash;35</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/11.21-23?lang=eng#20" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1 Ne. 11:21&ndash;23</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/7.47-48?lang=eng#46" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moro. 7:47&ndash;48</a>.) Let me illustrate:</p>
						<div class="figure">
	      <ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>Touched by the spirit of a visit, a less-active teenager expresses love for his parents, by whose love his heart is turned to God.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>A priesthood leader expresses love to a dissident group of less-active members, and twenty return to sacrament meeting that same day.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
	      </ol>
	    </div>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label"></span>
						<p><span class="emphasis">Share spiritual experiences. </span>Spiritual experiences have great impact upon men&rsquo;s souls. Share them as prompted by the Spirit. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/50.21-22?lang=eng#20" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 50:21&ndash;22</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/10.25-37?lang=eng#24" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Luke 10:25&ndash;37</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/acts/26.1-32?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Acts 26:1&ndash;32</a>.) For example:</p>
						<div class="figure">
	      <ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>A less-active husband tells two priesthood leaders of last night&rsquo;s dream. He repents that very evening as he recounts the experience.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>Two priesthood leaders tell an inspiring missionary story. As a result, two less-active sons are now serving missions.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
	      </ol>
	    </div>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label"></span>
						<p><span class="emphasis">Perform priesthood ordinances. </span>&ldquo;In the ordinances &hellip; , the power of godliness is manifest.&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.20?lang=eng#19" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 84:20</a>.) Bless the Saints. Bless the sick. Bless the homes of the Saints. Encourage others to seek for priesthood blessings. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/20.2-9?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 20:2&ndash;9</a>.) For example:</p>
						<div class="figure">
	      <ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>In an unscheduled visit by an institute director, a blessing is received by a college woman who has strayed into transgression. She is caused to remember God and returns to the institute.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>Another man is raised directly from his sickbed.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>A daughter receives a priesthood blessing and finds the peace that has eluded her since her father&rsquo;s death.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
	      </ol>
	    </div>
					</li>
				</ol>
      </div>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p46" class="">Brethren, these seven suggestions&mdash;one or more as needed&mdash;will always bring the Spirit of the Lord into your visits. Are these not some of the <span class="emphasis">spiritual gifts</span> that Christ gave that prepared the way for the Holy Ghost to testify and <span class="emphasis">change men&rsquo;s hearts?</span> Spiritually give of yourself and your visits will not then be routine, but you will discern the needs of the Saints. You will commit them in the Spirit to act. They will repent and come unto Christ.</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p47" class="">Yes, it&rsquo;s true, there are a few sheep who will not respond to their Master&rsquo;s voice, who are not willing at this time&mdash;and I repeat, <span class="emphasis">at this time</span>&mdash;to respond, because Jesus taught that He could only &ldquo;<span class="emphasis">bring</span> all <span class="emphasis">men</span> unto him, on <span class="emphasis">conditions of repentance.</span>&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.12?lang=eng#11" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 18:12</a>; italics added.)</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p48" class="">With those souls, we just go on loving them and try again at a later time when they may have a more repentant heart and will respond to the Spirit. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/18.32?lang=eng#31" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 18:32</a>.)</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h2>A Sister&rsquo;s Visits</h2>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p50" class="">May I share a personal experience of my wife. While on a stake conference assignment with me, she accompanied a Relief Society president on such a visit. As shepherds and servants of the Lord, they had tremendous success.</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p51" class="">Then, about a year later while I was teaching some priesthood brethren how to make such visits, a 35-year-old man told me of my wife&rsquo;s visit a year ago and said: &ldquo;May I tell you a secret? My entire family had decided the day before your wife came to visit that we were leaving the Church, offended, never to return. I bear witness to you that we felt the Lord speak through her as she stirred us up in remembrance of God and our ordinances. I&rsquo;m a member of a bishopric now. I would not be here today if it were not for her.&rdquo;</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p52" class="">He then smiled and said, &ldquo;How I wish now that I had more carefully watched her invite the Spirit upon me and my family, as it now falls upon me to go out tonight and do my very first home visit.&rdquo;</p>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p53" class="">Yes, brethren, the sisters can assist in this work also.</p>
			</div>
			<div>
				<h2>In Summary: The Divine Motivation</h2>
				<div class="figure">
	<p class="preamble">May I then summarize:</p>
	<ol class="number">
					
					<li>
						<span class="label">1.</span>
						<p>We are to be instruments in the Lord&rsquo;s hands to bring souls to Christ. Perhaps this is the greatest gift one man can bestow upon another.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label">2.</span>
						<p>We must better <span class="emphasis">relearn</span> how to invite the Spirit of the Lord for such an endeavor, even humbling self &ldquo;to the dust.&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138.56?lang=eng#55" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 138:56</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/34.38?lang=eng#37" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 34:38</a>.)</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label">3.</span>
						<p>The process described works for all men, young and old, who qualify with &ldquo;faith, hope, charity and love, with an eye single to the glory of God.&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/4.5?lang=eng#4" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 4:5</a>.) You young men, encourage your fathers and companions to hold such visits. You have a right to be shown how, and to motivate and teach us as well.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label">4.</span>
						<p>Remember, these suggestions are not meant to change the processes for home teaching, visiting teaching, or auxiliary visits, but are a suggested <span class="emphasis">means</span> for bringing the Spirit into all such visits.</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label">5.</span>
						<p>The process described for inviting the Spirit works the same with:</p>
						<div class="figure">
	      <ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>a rebellious child at home</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>a discouraged individual</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>an associate and</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>even yourself</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
		<li>
		  <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
		  <div class="" id="">
		    <p>as well as in visits to homes.</p>
		  </div>
		</li>
	      </ol>
	    </div>
					</li>
					<li>
						<span class="label">6.</span>
						<p>Let us commit as one leader did: &ldquo;There will not be one less-active member who has turned from God in my quorum or class. I will do all in my power to see that mighty change come into his heart.&rdquo;</p>
					</li>
				</ol>
      </div>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p67" class="">In conclusion, may I remind each of us that our motivation must not be just for duty, for the Church, or as a result of a calling we have, but our <span class="emphasis">divine motivation</span> must be for <a class="no-link-style" href="http://lds.org/general-conference/2009/10/the-love-of-god?lang=eng">the love of God</a>. Then will the miraculous results occur.</p>
				<div class="figure">
	<ol class="content-list alpha-caps">
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>&ldquo;Wax strong in the Spirit &hellip; ;</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>&ldquo;Teach with power and authority from God;</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>&ldquo;Receive the grace of God&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.26?lang=eng#25" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 18:26</a>); and</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>Be restored unto the grace we once had. (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/18.26?lang=eng#25" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 18:26</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/hel/12.24?lang=eng#23" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Hel. 12:24</a>.) And then</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	  <li>
	    <div class="" id="">&mdash;</div>
	    <div class="" id="">
	      <p>With that grace or enabling power of God, we might thereby obtain charity (see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.34,36?lang=eng#33" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Ether 12:34, 36</a>), &ldquo;even the pure love of Christ&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/7.47?lang=eng#46" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moro. 7:47</a>).</p>
	    </div>
	  </li>
	</ol>
      </div>
				<p uri="/ensign/1988/11/inviting-others-to-come-unto-christ.p74" class="">May that gift, even charity, be ours. May we give of ourselves to the spiritually needy the spiritual gifts Christ gave. I know of no greater joy that can come to man than &ldquo;the soul that repenteth.&rdquo; (See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/18.13-16?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 18:13&ndash;16</a>.) May the Lord bless us to learn how to bring men to Christ, and, in the process, <span class="emphasis">find Him ourselves,</span> I humbly pray, in the name of Jesus Christ, amen.</p>
			</div>
		
                            
                            
                            
